# Persistent Business Context

- Before starting work, check `.agent-memory/ORG_CONTEXT.md`, `.agent-memory/STAKEHOLDER_MAP.md`, `.agent-memory/DECISION_LOG.md`, `.agent-memory/PROCESS_PLAYBOOK.md`, `.agent-memory/BRAND_CONTEXT.md`, and the relevant `.agent-memory/FUNC_*.md`.
- The live documents, systems, and decisions are the source of truth; `.agent-memory/*.md` are fast-recovery cache contexts.
- Before brand / messaging / external-facing copy, always read `BRAND_CONTEXT.md` first.
- Before any decision or strategy work, read `DECISION_LOG.md` — a logged decision is the source of truth; do not silently contradict it.
- Before any work, identify every affected function and external party via `STAKEHOLDER_MAP.md`, and address all of them — never ship a partial answer.
- **Completeness**: never deliver only the happy path. Cover downstream effects, failure cases, and prerequisites, and name an owner + date for every action item.
- For anything external-facing, match `BRAND_CONTEXT.md` voice and respect legal/policy constraints; when unsure, flag it instead of guessing.
- After meaningful changes, add a record to `WORKING_LOG.md` and log non-trivial decisions in `DECISION_LOG.md`.
- When modifying `.agent-memory/` docs, always tell the user explicitly what changed.
